  "riddle": "1. Seek the river that courses through central India, renowned for its significant length — how many kilometers does it stretch?\n\n2. What hidden treasure lies in the prime factors of that very distance? Calculate their sum.\n\n3. This vast nation, teeming with life, holds the title of the second most populous in the world. Discover its population.\n\n4. As before, determine the essence of the number you just unveiled. What is the sum of its distinct prime factors?\n\n5. Find the tributary veiled in the mists of geography, whose waters feed into the larger stream of the region. Which river is it?\n\n6. Above the valley where this tributary flows, what is the elevation of the main river in meters?\n\n7. Often a haven for food lovers, how many restaurants can be found in close proximity to this riverside?\n\n8. Combine the height of the river you just discovered with the culinary options nearby — what is the absolute difference between them?\n\n9. As you navigate deeper, uncover once more the elevation of the main river. \n\n10. An adjacent river nestles against this one; into what larger body does it ultimately pour its waters?\n\n11. Ascend to the heavens and learn the elevation of the river that greets the reclaimed waters of nearby lakes. \n\n12. The banks of this flowing companion host not only flora but also places of knowledge — how many libraries exist in its shadow?\n\n13. Relate the elevation of this river you just examined with the number of libraries nearby. What is the absolute difference between those two figures?\n\n14. Chart your course and determine the driving distance between the river that has welcomed visitors for ages and your earlier focal stream. \n\n15. For the journey you’ve calculated, what is the total count of its divisors?\n\n16. Along the banks of the river that forms a boundary there lie towns; how many are they?\n\n17. In the network of wetlands, find the reference number tied to significant conservation efforts for a certain ecological area. \n\n18. Delve into the waters and find the length of a river that dances nearby; what measurement does its span claim in kilometers?\n\n19. Discover the year when a reservoir reflecting nature’s magnificence was declared a national treasure.\n\n20. What is the travel duration in minutes needed to transition from the expanse of the Pench to that of the serene Shipra?\n\n21. Engage in a deeper mathematical adventure: what is the digital root of your travel time from the last clue?\n\n22. Measure the length of the river that serves as a delicate boundary between states; how many kilometers does it stretch?\n\n23. Among the trees in a nearby wildlife sanctuary, what is the primary species that thrives there?\n\n24. Now, compute the following: What is the result of (the length from clue 1, plus the population from clue 3, plus the towns from clue 16) modulo 10?",
